Abuja (Sundiata Post) – A chartered accountant who lived in the US for 45 years was allegedly murdered at his retirement country-home in Ikorodu area of Lagos State, a few months after he returned from the U.S. Identified as Mutiu Agbosasa, it was gathered that he had arrived home after an outing at the “Island Club” in Lagos when he was attacked by assassins. The corpse of
the deceased was allegedly butchered and placed in his car, which was set
ablaze by the assailants. Sharing the
story, some neighbours and close residents took to Facebook to lament on the
incident. See Photos Here: Culled from Information Nigeria